The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, June 17, 2004 				 Music for the soul
																								That Swami Vivekananda had a keen interest in Indian classical music and practised it actively himself are well-known facts. In remembrance of the great visionarys devotion to this art form, The Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture hosts concerts in Indian classical music from time to time. Todays sarod recital by Basant Kabra of the Maihar Senia gharana offers an opportunity to witness a performance that owes its allegiance to a rich musical heritage as well as individual genius. Having received intensive talim from the celebrated Annapurna Devi, Kabras recital is marked by a detailed playing of the alap and jod with a step-by-step unfolding of the raga. This evening he will be accompanied by Amitava Gain on the tabla.																								Event: Sarod recital by Basant Kabra																								When: Today at 6 pm																								Where: The Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Vivekananda Hall
